    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Metal money in the form of metal wire, often copper or brass, cut in lenghts and stored in bundles or loose, introduced into Africa by European traders as trade money.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046750/Contributed as a candidate scope note</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Moneda metálica en la forma de un cable metálico, frecuentemente cobre o bronce, cortado a lo largo y almacenado en bultos o suelto, introducido en África por comerciantes europeos como moneda comercial.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Metaalgeld in de vorm van metaaldraad, vaak koper of messing, in stukken gezaagd en in bundels of los bewaard; werd door Europese kooplieden in Afrika geïntroduceerd als ruilmiddel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>通常由銅或黃銅等金屬線製的金屬貨幣，切成一截截，捆裝或零散貯存。由歐洲商人引進非洲，作為交易貨幣使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
